# 🏉 AFL Data Analysis Project

## ✨ About This Project

This project is a simple and practical analysis of AFL (Australian Football League) data.
I worked on transforming raw match and player data into meaningful insights using SQL and Power BI.

It helped me understand how real-world data is messy, and how to clean, structure, and analyze it properly.

---

## 🎯 What I Did

* Cleaned and structured raw AFL dataset
* Built relational tables (teams, players, matches, player stats)
* Wrote SQL queries to explore performance
* Created insights on teams and players

---

## 🧱 Data Model

The data was organized into:

* **Teams** → team details
* **Players** → player info with team mapping
* **Matches** → match-level data
* **Player Stats** → performance per match

---

## 📊 Key Insights

* Identified top goal scorers
* Found most active players (based on disposals)
* Analyzed team performance and wins
* Explored close matches and margins

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used

* SQL Server
* SQL
* Power BI

